The course is primarily focused on critically ill patient. Students will learn about the organization of emergency medicine, the management of life-threatening conditions, principles of emergency surgery and management of severe trauma. Skills for adult cardio-pulmonary resuscitation will be obtained. Students will be involved in everyday work of department of intensive care and they will present summary of case report at examination. Knowledge and skills acquired during the course will prepare the student for the practice in emergency department, which is in the programme of 6th study year.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Management of critically ill is the most important part of emergency medicine. The recognition, differential diagnosis and primary treatment of the critically ill patient is at main focus of the course. The aim is to teach: 
1) organisation of emergency medicine, including patient triage principles; 
2) management of  life-threatening syndromes (shock, acute respiratory failure, acute renal failure acute, cardiac arrhythmias, sepsis, and coma);
3) principles of emergency surgery, including trauma.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course the student:
-  is able to recognize critical illness of the patient;
-  is able perform primary management of critical conditions;
-  knows the organisation of emergency medicine, including triage at emergency
   department;
-  knows the primary management principles of severe trauma in hospital;
-  knows the principles of emergency surgery;
-  recognizes life-threatening arrhythmias and is able to treat them;
-  is able to perform cardio-pulmonary resuscitation of an adult;
-  is able to present the case history in short and concise way.
